          "type": "text",
          "name": "help_text",
          "value": "**Rich tasks** These tasks dive deeply into material using flexible and engaging explorations taking 1 to 3 class periods.\n\n**Open-Ended versus Problem-Solving Tasks** Open-ended tasks explore with more loosely-defined endpoints in mind and with a greater range of possible answers along the way.  Problem-solving tasks have very well-defined goals and usually just a small set of answers. Both types invite lots of exploration, play, and discussion, and there is overlap between the two.\n\n**Journeys** All rich tasks provide opportunities for further explorations. Which questions do your students think of along the way and at the end? Keep track of their questions and use them as further tasks to be pursued. This give your students deeper experiences as mathematicians, and it gives them more agency and engagement.",
          "_translations": {
            "value": {}
          },
          "parameter_list": {
            "icon_src": "help",
            "style": "navigation"
          },
          "_nested_name": "dg_info.help_text"
